oai_dc:dc.dc:subject: Soldiers; Tunnels; Canals; War; World War, 1914-1914
oai_dc:dc.dc:description: Group of about ten soldiers at the south end of the Hindenburg Tunnel where the St. de Quentin Canal ran through, east of Bellicourt, France. The photograph was taken from the interior of the tunnel and the soldiers are shown walking across planking; over the canal.
